Kamienna Wola  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Gowarczów, within Końskie County, Świętokrzyskie Voivodeship, in south-central Poland. It lies approximately  north of Gowarczów,  north of Końskie, and  north of the regional capital Kielce.
